name: kristen bell
description:
[Verified, #Repost @jessicajcourtney (@get_repost)
„Éª„Éª„Éª
I was in her shoes only a few years ago, but my story ended very differently.
.
I was out shopping in the local bazaar, a place we had been a hundred times before. It was one of the kids‚Äô favorite things to do on the weekend. We were walking from the toy section across the street to the vegetable stands and all the sudden a riot broke out in the square where we were standing. I ran into the alley away from the crowd and the police shooting tear gas dragging the kids with me to try and be anywhere else, somewhere safe for my kids.
.
We ran by the onion and pumpkin stand and the men behind the counter called us into their shop and shuttered the doors to keep out the gas. The kids were shaking, terrified, and had no idea what was going on. The shutters were pinging on the outside around us. But inside this little market booth with aluminum doors drawn shut, these kind strangers were offering candy and sugar-filled tea to calm our nerves, protecting both our bodies and our hearts from harm.
.
About an hour later, they opened the shutters in the silence and went out to check if it was safe. I told them my car was across the street and they quickly recommended that I leave the car and take a taxi from the back side of the bazaar. Then they left their stall to see us safely to the taxi. .
In every time of fear or attack that I have experienced while living in one of the most war-torn countries of my lifetime, a stranger has been there to care, console, and provide cover. My children have always been of their utmost concern.
.
So today, I woke up to images of this mom just looking for safety for her little ones and my heart broke. I wish she could be met with welcome, shutters closing out the dark and sweet tea to calm her nerves. I wish she could say to her babies, ‚Äúlook how nice everyone is here, look how they protect us even though they don‚Äôt know us.‚Äù I wish she could just have someone come alongside her and ask what she needs and what she dreams for her families future.

#webelongtoeachother #sisterhood]

URGENT: Know this name. Jemel Roberson.
The U.S. is awash in mass shootings. It‚Äôs been just 2 weeks since another gunman slaughtered 11 senior citizens at a synagogue in Pittsburgh. Just this past week 12 people were gunned down in a bar in CA.
300 more mass shootings have happened this year. 300.
And the primary response for how we stop these shootings continues to be to be ‚Äúgood guys w/guns‚Äù intervening & stopping the bad guys. Except the CA shooter killed the good guy w/a gun, a veteran cop, who bravely entered the bar to save those under attack.
And now on Sun morn, w/the threat of another mass shooting underway, yet another good guy w/a gun was shot & killed‚Äìthis time by police. He was black.
26 yr old Jemel Roberson of Chicago, was a beloved church musician who played drums & keyboard for churches all over the city. Like most local church musicians, he had another job to help pay the bills. He worked as an armed security guard for clubs & bars. W/the mass shooting in the bar in Thousand Oaks, CA just days earlier, security guards across the country in similar venues were on high alert.
At 4AM on Sunday morn, at Manny‚Äôs Blue Room Bar in the small town of Robbins, Illinois, Jemel Roberson was forced to ask a group of drunk men to leave the bar. Suddenly, according to witnesses, one of the men came back with a gun into the bar and opened fire.
Enter the good guy with a gun.
Jemel Roberson bravely entered the fray, returned fire, then chased a man down outside, & held him down until police arrived. Family & friends say that he hoped to become a police officer himself one day.
Right now we should be hearing abt Jemel Roberson the hero, refused to allow people to harmed on his watch, & bravely brought a gunman to justice.
But this is America. & what we are all seeing is that being a ‚Äúgood guy with a gun,‚Äù while black, might get u killed black, might get u killed by ppl who simply cannot imagine u are there to help.
As WGN reported, "everyone was screaming out 'hes a security guard!' & they basically saw a blk man w/a gun & killed him". He thwarted the worst danger from the earlier shooting, only to be murdered.]

This Sunday, please take a moment to watch what u have done. Its working. Our families are being reunited. YOU DID THIS.

Yolany Padilla‚Äìwho fled violence in Honduras to seek legal asylum in the US--is one of them. Her 6-yr-old son Jelsin was taken from her by ICE two months ago. YESTERDAY, YOUR FUNDS SECURED JELSIN‚ÄôS RETURN TO YOLANYS ARMS.

To imagine how it feels to be her. How it feels to be her son.
You did that. You dared to do what many refuse to do. You dared to imagine how it would feel to have your baby taken from your arms and not know if you‚Äôll ever see him again. You dared to imagine and that imagining broke your heart.

name: kristen bell
description:
[Verified, #Repost @glennondoyle (@get_repost)
„Éª„Éª„Éª
Here‚Äôs what the executive order does and doesn‚Äôt do: The executive order stops the new bleeding. But it does not address the blood on their hands.
The president has just signed an executive order reversing his own policy of mass family separation at the border.
This executive order was signed because OF YOU. This administration took a bet that America had no more unifying non-negotiables ‚Äì that there was nothing we wouldn‚Äôt tolerate ‚Äì that we wouldn‚Äôt care enough to keep fighting. They lost that bet. We cared enough. When it came to the babies we, the people, came together and said: NOT THIS.
We need to take a moment to acknowledge your victory.
Okay that moment is over. Because this remains a national crisis and atrocity.
This order does not change the President‚Äôs zero-tolerance regime. Every unauthorized border crossing (even those who may be seeking asylum legally) will continue to be treated as a federal crime. Families may be detained by (in for-profit facilities) indefinitely while the adults face federal prosecution.
IT DOES NOTHING WITH RESPECT TO THE THOUSANDS OF CHILDREN ALREADY FORCIBLY REMOVED FROM THEIR FAMILIES through this barbaric policy. NOTHING ABOUT THEM. We have learned today that children have been flown all over the country ‚Äì hundreds of miles from their parents, and authorities have said there is a high probability that many will never be reunited. We learned today that several of the FOR-PROFIT companies that house unaccompanied children have histories of sexual misconduct and other abuse.
ORPHANED & ABUSED BY OUR GOVERNMENT.
TOGETHER RISING WILL NOT REST UNTIL THESE CHILDREN ARE BACK IN THEIR PARENTS‚Äô ARMS.
We will not forget about these thousands of terrified children. We will reunify these families.
Every boots on the ground organization with which are in daily contact tells us this: These babies need advocates to help get them reunified with their families. We are going to keep HELPING THE HELPERS. We are going to lock arms with these organizations and keep walking with then until the babies are returned.
We will do this together. Please give at the link in my bio ‚òùüèº
G & @together.rising]
